section class="hero container-fluid"
  div class="intro col-md-5 col-md-offset-4 col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1"
    h1 We're the Nashville chapter of the National Stuttering Association, meeting once a month to support each other and talk about stuttering.
    div class="clearfix"
    div class="col-md-5 col-md-offset-4 col-sm-3 col-sm-offset-4 col-xs-10 col-xs-offset-2"
      input type="button" class="hero-button" value="Find out more"

section class="section container-fluid"
  div class="section-left section-boxes col-md-6 col-md-offset-1 col-xs-10 col-xs-offset-1"
    = link_to 'Read our stories, and stay updated â†’', blog_path, class: 'section-header-font'
    p class="base-font"
      |
        Beyond our regular monthly meetings, our members make posts about their experiences with stuttering. Whether they themselves stutter, or they are or have been a SLP (speech-language pathologist), each person has had personal/professional experience with stuttering and offer unique insights of it. Feel free to read a few posts, comment on some, or submit your own!

section class="section container-fluid"
  div class="section-left section-boxes col-md-6 col-md-offset-1 col-xs-10 col-xs-offset-1"
    div id="map"
  div class="section-right section-boxes meeting col-md-4 col-xs-10"
    h2 class="section-header-font" Where we meet
    p class="base-font"
      |
        On the third Tuesday of each month, our chapter of the National Stuttering Association meets at Glen Leven Presbyterian Church off of Franklin Road in Nashville, TN. Meetings typically start at 6pm and end at around 8pm.
    p class="base-font"
      |
        For more information, click on the red marker inside the map.

